.:: Puzzle 6x3-Level-6-19::.
There are 3 different favourite beverages: lemonade, milk, cola
The people have 3 different jobs:  scientist, mechanic, bartender
There are 3 different nationalities: australian, indian, italian
3 different pets are kept: fish, ferret, frog
The people prefer 3 different types of sport: badminton, handball, biathlon
The people use 3 different means of transport: car, bike, roller
 1. the indian is not the person drinking lemonade##6
 2. the person driving the roller is between the person driving the car and the person who's sport is handball##2
 3. the italian is not the owner of the fish##6
 4. the scientist is not the person driving the bike##6
 5. the scientist is somewhere to the left of the person who's sport is biathlon##5
 6. the person drinking cola is somewhere to the right of the owner of the frog##5
 7. the person driving the car is the italian##1
 8. the person driving the bike is the person who's sport is handball##1
 9. the australian is on the right of the mechanic##1
10. the owner of the fish is on the left or right of the person who's sport is badminton##3
11. the person driving the roller is not the person who's sport is biathlon##6
12. the person drinking lemonade is on the right of the mechanic##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |      1      |    2     |       3        |
| Beverage      | milk | lemonade      | cola          |
| Job           | mechanic | scientist | bartender |
| Nationality   | indian      | australian  | italian        |
| Pet           | fish         | frog    | ferret            |
| Sport         | handball      | badminton     | biathlon         |
| Transport     | bike       | roller    | car            |

